You are given an array of integers. An element is called a leader if it is greater than or equal to all the elements to its right side. Your task is to print all the leader elements in the array.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer n, representing the size of the array.

The second line contains n space-separated integers, representing the array elements.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

Print all the leader elements in the array, separated by space.

Sample Input 0

6
16 17 4 3 5 2
Sample Output 0

17 5 2
Explanation 0

Leaders are 17, 5, 2 because each is greater than or equal to all elements to its right.

Sample Input 1

5
10 9 8 7 6
Sample Output 1

10 9 8 7 6
Explanation 1

All elements are leaders since each one is greater than everything to its right.


import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
       int n=sc.nextInt();
       int arr[]=new int[n];
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
       {
        arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
       }
       ArrayList <Integer>list=new ArrayList<>();
       int l=arr[n-1];
       list.add(l);
       for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--)
       {
        if(arr[i]>l)
        {
            l=arr[i];
            list.add(l);
        }
       }
       Collections.reverse(list);
       for(int i: list)
        System.out.print(i+" ");
    }
}

